    "attestationText" : {
      "text" : "<p><b>I am capable of managing medical conditions typically encountered in the practice of Pediatric Hospital Medicine* to the level of Pediatric medicine training including the medical co-management of patients hospitalized for surgical disorders.</b></p><p style='margin-top: 15px;'><span style='color: red; font-weight: bold;'>*</span> These include but are not restricted to: Abdominal Pain, Acute Renal Failure, Acute Respiratory Failure, Acid/Base Disturbance, Alcohol and Drug Intoxication / Withdrawal, Altered Mental Status, Allergic Reaction, Anemia, Ascites, Asthma, Cardiac Arrhythmia, Cellulitis, Chest Pain, Child Abuse and Neglect, Cholecystitis, Colitis, Congestive Heart Failure, Dehydration, Diabetes Mellitus, Diarrhea, Dizziness, Electrolyte disturbance, Fever, Gastrointestinal Bleed, Headache, Hepatic Diseases, Hypertension, Infections, Kawasaki Disease, Kidney/Ureteral Stone, Meningitis / Encephalitis, Nausea with Vomiting, Osteomyelitis, Pancreatitis, Pericarditis, Poisoning, Psychiatric Disturbance, Pneumonia, Seizure, Shock, Sickle Cell Disease, Sepsis Syndrome, Small Bowel Obstruction / Ileus, Stroke, Suicidal Behavior, Syncope, Thyroid Dysfunction, Urinary Tract Infection, Venous Thromboembollism and Weakness.</p>"
